    "single_title_and_text_GYC4Nn": {
      "type": "single-title_and_text",
      "name": "Title and Text",
      "settings": {
        "title": "",
        "text": "<p></p><p>Elsewhere, the Luna Turquoise tablecloth was styled beneath a beautiful walkway draped in white wisteria. The combination of green and white, layered with moody shade-loving plants and green Moroccan ceramics, captured the feeling of an elegant midsummer lunch in the garden.</p><p>Finally, the Peony Urn Pastel tablecloth was nestled amongst clipped architectural hedges, where incredible peonies created a true focal point amongst the greenery. At this time of year, when so many of us are eagerly waiting for our own peonies to bloom, it felt like such a treat to photograph these abundant, open flowers in all their fleeting beauty — perfectly capturing the joyful spirit of early summer entertaining.</p>",
        "font_type": "body",
        "vertical_alignment": "center",
        "alignment": "center",
        "color_scheme": "dark_text",
        "margin_top": "none",
        "margin_bot": "none"
      }
